-- Oil Price Rise Partly Due to Speculation, Qatar Oil Minister Attiyah Says
-- B y   D a h l i a   K h o l a i f
-- 2010-10-10T12:44:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/oil-price-rise-partly-due-to-speculation-qatar-oil-minister-attiyah-says.html
The recent increase in oil prices is
“partly due to speculation,” Qatar’s oil minister said.  Oil at $70 to $80 a barrel is good for consumers and
producers, Abdullah bin Hamad al-Attiyah said in Kuwait today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
